{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/background-information/sources-of-carbon-monoxide/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"d869bfc6-3f51-5fb9-83ab-a43d2cdac8d4","slug":"sources-of-carbon-monoxide","fullItemName":"Sources of carbon monoxide","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field 46d90a44-8699-444a-82e4-a8f900868bc3 --><h2>What are the potential sources of carbon monoxide?</h2><!-- end field 46d90a44-8699-444a-82e4-a8f900868bc3 -->","summary":"","htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item 9ea7bb87-f6f9-4bc4-9024-a8f900868a7b --><!-- begin field 56cc433b-594a-4e76-9206-a8f900868bc3 --><ul><li><strong>Exposure to carbon monoxide may occur:</strong><ul><li>When fuel burning appliances are poorly installed, faulty, not maintained or used inappropriately.<ul><li>Chimneys or flues are blocked.</li><li>There is a lack of ventilation in the room.</li><li>Gas ovens are used inappropriately for heating.</li><li>Barbecues are used inside homes, caravans or tents for cooking or heating.</li><li>Oversized pots are used on gas cooker rings.</li></ul></li><li>If shisha pipes are used in poorly ventilated rooms.</li><li>If petrol or diesel engine exhaust gases are retained in an enclosed space, for example, from vehicles or portable generators.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Other sources for carbon monoxide include:</strong><ul><li>Smoke in burning buildings.</li><li>Paint removers.</li><li>Aerosol propellants.</li><li>Neighbouring property with an appliance which is producing carbon monoxide.</li></ul></li><li><strong>Signs that indicate incomplete combustion may be taking place, releasing carbon monoxide, include:</strong><ul><li>Yellow or orange rather than blue flames (except fuel effect fires or flueless appliances which display this colour flame).</li><li>Soot or yellow/brown staining around or on appliances.</li><li>Pilot lights which frequently blow out.</li><li>Increased condensation inside windows.</li></ul></li></ul><p>[<a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/references/\">HSE, 2011</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/references/\">CMO and CNO, 2013</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/references/\">PHE, 2016a</a>; <a class=\"bibliography-reference internal-reference\" href=\"/topics/carbon-monoxide-poisoning/references/\">BMJ, 2017</a>] </p><!-- end field 56cc433b-594a-4e76-9206-a8f900868bc3 --><!-- end item 9ea7bb87-f6f9-4bc4-9024-a8f900868a7b -->","topic":{"id":"c7d4e6f1-4a64-54dd-be29-5ad7634dc8fc","topicId":"805e4b0d-7153-46dc-ad0e-078747029014","topicName":"Carbon monoxide poisoning","slug":"carbon-monoxide-poisoning","lastRevised":"Last revised in October 2018","chapters":[{"id":"a4fe1221-5744-5f22-a201-02e8b266911e","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"828b1d0e-ea18-5f96-b42a-c314ceef8855","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"9fca25de-4ad7-587a-b4b5-6f05a504ccdb","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"9ed23aaf-6330-5d0c-98c7-1278da260d26","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"2a5a9598-8906-5dcc-b576-387cf1cb47e8","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"d52b952b-ba10-536f-8e68-fef415d54a86","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"d3be2eb0-7aa4-5858-b2b8-b72c4681c4f8","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"b514d89c-b8b3-54dc-ad36-ddbc2722d0bb","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"7845409f-b34c-5740-b2eb-b0a700dea3a3","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit criteria"},{"id":"6e946cc3-972d-5e8f-95dc-64b2d7a56a56","slug":"qof-indicators","fullItemName":"QOF indicators"},{"id